de.wwu.muggl.ui.gui.windows
Class FastExecutionWindow

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.ui.gui.windows.FastExecutionWindow
All Implemented Interfaces:
ShellWindow
public class FastExecutionWindow
extends java.lang.Object
implements ShellWindow

The fast execution window is used in step by step execution mode. It is initialized with a number of instructions that will not be executed step by step. In fact, they will be executed as fast as possible. The execution speed should be similar to the direct execution. Once the number of instructions has been executed or execution in the virtual machine has finished, fast executed will stop.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-11
Author:
Tim Majchrzak
